{
  "name": "highland",
  "description": "A pan flute breathing across a sunlit mountain meadow, hollow and airy and calm. Round breathy pipe tones with soft air-noise and gentle overblow rise over a low bamboo ground: a melody pan-flute swelling in on the breath, a brighter whistle-pipe echoing across the valley, a warm low-pipe cushion, a distant pipe-harmonic call, tiny top-octave breath-flicks on the wind, a lush breath-pad bloom, a shimmering breathy chord-cloud, the mountain breeze itself, and a happy little birdcall flick. A major pentatonic, additive only, hall reverb. Highland and Andean calm — open, bright, and uplifted, peaceful but never lonely, never dreary.",
